<TITLE> Graft charges framed against Pankaj, wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 27 (bdnews24.com)Charges were framed against Awami Swechchhasevak League general secretary Pankaj Debnath and wife Monica Debnath Tuesday. Judge Firoz Alam of the Special Judge's Court set Sunday for recording 38 separate witness statements. On March 22, Anticorruption Commission (ACC) director Abdul Latif filed the case against Pankaj and his wife with Dhanmondi Police Station. The couple are charged with incorporating false information in their wealth statements, submitted to the ACC, and having assets beyond their known sources of income. According to the case statement Pankaj acquired assets, exceeding his legitimate income, of Tk 65.16 lakh, including FDRs worth Tk 32 lakh. Monica is accused of abetting in the acquisition of the assets. Pankaj was brought to court from Dhaka Central Jail to hear the charges. His wife's whereabouts remains unknown. bdnew
